    <bioghist>Governor of Michigan, 1855-1886; U.S. Secretary of War, 1887-1897; U.S. Senator, 1902-1907.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Pages torn from letterpress volume of copies of outgoing correspondence of Alger serving as governor of Michigan. The letters concern railway dispute between the Detroit, Lansing &amp; Northern Railroad and the Toledo, Ann Arbor &amp; North Michigan Railway Company. There are also letters regarding prisons, and the state training schools for young men and women, the development of the Upper Peninsula, etc. Many of the letters are badly faded.</scopecontent>
